This paper analyzes the propagation behavior of users on social media, specifically Twitter, in response to news sources spreading trusted versus malicious content. The study involves a large-scale analysis of 11 million posts and considers population versus subpopulation behavior, demographics, and the types of propagation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
